 French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Stapleford was born in 1240, in Stapleford, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Robert Stapleford le Bruen. She had at least 2 daughters with John Palmer. She died in 1334, in Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 94."},"et":{"1240–1334":"1240–1334","1238–Male":"1238–Surnud","1265–Female":"1265–Surnud","–1313":"–1313","1220–1260":"1220–1260","1238":"1238","1313":"1313","1334":"1334","1265":"1265","1220":"1220","1240":"1240","1260":"1260","Feb 1313":"veebruar 1313","Nottingham":"Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Stapleford, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Stapleford, Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Whatton in the Vale, Nottinghamshire,England":"Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1240–1334":"1240–1334","1238–Male":"1238–Kuollut","1265–Female":"1265–Kuollut","–1313":"–1313","1220–1260":"1220–1260","1238":"1238","1313":"1313","1334":"1334","1265":"1265","1220":"1220","1240":"1240","1260":"1260","Feb 1313":"helmikuu 1313","Nottingham":"Nottinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Stapleford, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Stapleford, Nottinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Whatton in the Vale, Nottinghamshire,England":"Nottinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"